{
  "answer": "**The line \"Cheen o Arab hamara, Hindustaan hamara\" is the opening of Allama Iqbal's poem *Tarana-e-Milli* (*The National Song*), from *Bang-e-Dara Part 3* (chapter 23).**[^1]\n\nThis is the first line in the transliteration (Romanized Urdu) variant of the poem, followed by \"Muslim hain hum, watan hai saara jahan hamara\". (Note the minor spelling variations from your query: \"Cheen o Arab\" without hyphen, and \"Hindustaan\" rather than \"Hindostan\", which is standard in Romanized Urdu.)[^1]\n\nThe full opening stanza reads:\n\n> Cheen o Arab hamara, Hindustaan hamara  \n> Muslim hain hum, watan hai saara jahan hamara[^1]\n\nAn English translation begins: \"From Chin to Arab lands, our story flows, / The whole wide world's the home a Muslim knows.\"[^2]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, ch. 23 \"Tarana-e-Milli\" (transliteration), [p-56247d](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/23-tarana-e-milli/transliteration/#p-56247d).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, ch. 23 \"Tarana-e-Milli\" (translation), [p-8a4681](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/23-tarana-e-milli/translation/#p-8a4681).",
